				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Swarm Kiting Question<a name="51668"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 1:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been swarm kiting and seem to have a problem with some of my mobs not sticking to my pet. Three or four will start beating on him, but one or two will wander over to me and chase me around. 
<br />

<br />
I can keep running and chanting them down, but then I forget my pet  :p. So is this ok, or should they all stick to my pet?
<br />

<br />
Also, it's it a good idea to let your pet break on it's own and then switch to a target with more health and make him your pet next? I tend to do it that way, rather than charm the same guy and possibly lose him by not breaking the charm in time (you know... since I'm busy running from the stray mobs! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> )</span></td>
