				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been swarming for about five levels now so here is my input to the issues raised in this thread.
<br />

<br />
First, looting does not cause the pack to break from the pet, nor does buffing / healing.  I have a SS BP and have healed myself while the pet is getting beatdown,  I also use SoW potions.  I have had charm break when I buff/heal, rarely, but not enough to say it causes enough agro for the mobs to break off the pet.
<br />

<br />
Second, the largest swarm I had was 12 mobs.  When I would stick the pet on a mob, I would still have majority of the mobs on my tail.  So, I would kite them very close to the pet, be careful the pet's target will hit you if you get to close.  The mobs chasing you should stick the pet, sometimes it takes a couple runs past the pet, but eventually they will agro the pet.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
