				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting Question<a name="53338"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 11:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For my swarming abilities something i have noticed is the target nearest mob in swarm and charm it then hit attack right after.  What happens then if u time it just correctly is it will target next nearest mob (via cycle), auto attack with ur pet, and if this is done properly it should be the first two mobs in the swarm then all the mobs gain the aggro on it and i rarely have to make a second pass (only time ive found i had to do this was in GoD because the pathing is horrific and the mobs are all over the place.)
<br />

<br />

<br />
BTW figured i might as well give u my keyboard setup.  I have gone from level 34 to level 51 since like monday without any wrist problems due to my binds being very close together and i dont have to move my hand.
<br />

<br />
Forward = w
<br />
Left = s
<br />
Back = d
<br />
Right = f
<br />
Stopsong = w
<br />
Targetself/castgoblin ring/ retarget last target = r
<br />
Toggle last target = q
<br />
Auto attack = a (prolly gunna change this_
<br />
Auto run = v
<br />
Hail = g (for situations where i need to zone via magus)
<br />
Target nearest target = T
<br />
Everything else i click with my mouse button ie switching insturments/weapons, Casting songs (i do this via hotbuttons.  The UI i use is incredibly compact so i have about 95% visibility on my screen because of my custom UI while in the 640 resolution)  I use compact backpacks w/ insturments, My hotbutton has insturments but i modded it and change the slots it gives u (which is six slots) i keep my actions window minimized at all time via the o in the upper left hand corner.  And small/compact windows for everything else.  As for things like chatboxes and stuff i make it invisible via alpha background and change it to 0% i can still see all my text fine from the invisible stuff)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Basically what im saying is find a setup for ur keyboard that doesnt require much movment from ur hand and hitting the keys will become second nature w/ practice and u can concentrate on screen rather then the keys ur hittings.</span></td>
